==English==
===Etymology===
Hindi '''[[मसाला]]''' (masālā) "spice(s)", from Farsi '''[[مصالح]]''' (maṣāliḥ) "affairs, materials, spices", plural of '''[[ﺕﺤﻠﺼﻤ]]''' (maṣlaḥat) "affair, policy, best thing to do", both from Arabic, derived from '''[[صلح]]''' (ṣalaḥa) "be fit, competent, usable".  

===Noun===
'''masala'''
# a paste used in Indian cuisine